<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcc301041-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s44931"><num value="44931">§ 44931.</num><heading> Authority to exempt</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Homeland Security may grant an exemption from a regulation prescribed in carrying out sections 44901, 44903, 44906, 44909(c), and 44935–44937 of this title when the Secretary decides the exemption is in the public interest.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcc301042-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/115/254/dK/tI/s1991/j/1">Pub. L. 115–254, div. K, title I, § 1991(j)(1)</ref>, <date date="2018-10-05">Oct. 5, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/3645">132 Stat. 3645</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcc301043-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">
